The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 17: The government today said it could take more steps such as reducing customs duties to check rising prices and bring down the inflation rate to below 5 per cent. I am not happy with inflation... We are willing to take further fiscal steps (to contain inflation) if members so suggest, finance minister P. Chidambaram told the Lok Sabha.

 New Delhi, May 17: A head-hunting committee will hold interviews for the top job at the Oil and Natural Gas Corporation on June 5 and 6. The search committee, headed by N.K. Sinha, chairman of the Public Enterprise Selection Board, will interview 27 candidates for the chairmans post.

 New Delhi, May 17: Reliance Communication, Tata Teleservices and other CDMA operators have approached TDSAT seeking refund of the excess fee charged during 2003-06 because of the late implementation of the revenue sharing regime in allocation of spectrum.

 New Delhi, May 17: The government may be forced to pay penalties as it is yet to make arrangements to transport the crude that Cairn will start pumping from its Rajasthan fields from 2009. 

 Mumbai, May 17: Suzlon will raise $300 million through the issue of foreign currency convertible bonds, proposed to be listed on the Singapore Stock Exchange.




